der-layer','0'),(111,12,'mfn-post-hide-title','1'),(112,12,'mfn-post-remove-padding','1'),(113,12,'mfn-post-custom-layout','0'),(114,12,'mfn-post-one-page','0'),(115,12,'mfn-post-menu','0'),(116,12,'slide_template','default'),(117,12,'mfn-page-items',''),(118,12,'mfn-page-items-seo','Heading + desc\n<h1>Services</h1>\r\n[divider height=\"15\"]\r\n<p>Book at your favored time and experience the best treatment and service provided by our specialists.</p>\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n\n<img src=\"http://richmonddental.iugale.tech/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/home_healthy_pic19.png\" alt=\"\"/>\ncenter\n\nHeading + desc\n<h2>Our features</h2>\ncenter\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n\nBox\n[image src=\"http://richmonddental.iugale.tech/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Lanap.png\"]\r\n[divider height=\"25\"]\r\n<h3>Lanap</h3>\r\n[divider height=\"10\"]\r\n<p align=\"justify\">LANAP, or Laser Assisted New Attachment Procedure, is a form of periodontal therapy used to treat periodontitis. Unlike traditional surgeries, which involve the removal of both diseased and healthy gum tissues, LANAP specifically targets infected areas of the gums – leaving healthy tissues behind.</p>\ncenter\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n30px 15% 15px\nborder-right: 1px solid #eff6fa;\n\nBox\n[image src=\"http://richmonddental.iugale.tech/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Inlays-and-Onlays.png\"]\r\n[divider height=\"25\"]\r\n<h3>Inlays and onlays</h3>\r\n[divider height=\"10\"]\r\n<p align=\"justify\">Inlays and onlays are dental restorations that are more extensive than dental fillings but less so than caps and crowns. They are typically formed in a dental lab and are made of gold, porcelain or resin depending on the patient’s needs and aesthetic goals. </p>\ncenter\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n30px 15% 15px\nborder-right: 1px solid #eff6fa;\n\nBox\n[image src=\"http://richmonddental.iugale.tech/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Full-Mouth-Restoration.png\"]\r\n[divider height=\"25\"]\r\n<h3>Full Mouth Restoration</h3>\r\n[divider height=\"10\"]\r\n<p align=\"justify\">A full mouth restoration offers patients who have experienced a variety of dental traumas. From those who grind their teeth (bruxism) to those who have had oral cancer to drug users looking for a fresh start,will improve both the aesthetics of your mouth and the function. </p>\ncenter\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n30px 15% 15px\n\ndefault\n\nBox\n[image src=\"http://richmonddental.iugale.tech/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/zoom-teeth-whitening.png\"]\r\n[divider height=\"25\"]\r\n<h3>Zoom! teeth whitening</h3>\r\n[divider height=\"10\"]\r\n<p align=\"justify\">According to the American Academy of Cosmetic Dentistry, nearly 100 percent of Americans believe that a beautiful smile is an important social asset. Your smile is the first impression that others have of you, so why hide it?</p>\ncenter\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n30px 15% 15px\nborder-right: 1px solid #eff6fa;\n\nBox\n[image src=\"http://richmonddental.iugale.tech/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Nitrous-Oxide.png\"]\r\n[divider height=\"25\"]\r\n<h3>Nitrous Oxide</h3>\r\n[divider height=\"10\"]\r\n<p align=\"justify\">It is estimated that between 9 and 15% of American adults avoid going to the dentist because of fear. Studies show that fear of the dentist is more often due to society’s misplaced belief that dental treatments are all painful more so than an actual painful experience.</p>\ncenter\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n30px 15% 15px\nborder-right: 1px solid #eff6fa;\n\nBox\n[image src=\"http://richmonddental.iugale.tech/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Root-Canals.png\"]\r\n[divider height=\"25\"]\r\n<h3>Root Canals</h3>\r\n[divider height=\"10\"]\r\n<p align=\"justify\">Root canals are valuable dental procedures used to treat and preserve teeth with badly infected roots. The pulp is the live portion of the tooth that extends into the root and contains nerve endings and tissues. When it becomes infected, patients can experience pain, swelling and even total tooth loss unless treated.</p>\ncenter\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n30px 15% 15px\n\ndefault\n\nBox\n[image src=\"http://richmonddental.iugale.tech/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Invisalign.png\"]\r\n[divider height=\"25\"]\r\n<h3>Invisalign (Clear Braces)</h3>\r\n[divider height=\"10\"]\r\n<p align=\"justify\">Invisalign is an orthodontic appliance system used to inconspicuously treat crooked and crowded teeth in adults and teens. This modern take on braces features a system of clear aligner trays that are worn at all times with the exception of during meals and when brushing or flossing.</p>\ncenter\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n30px 15% 15px\nborder-right: 1px solid #eff6fa;\n\nBox\n[image src=\"http://richmonddental.iugale.tech/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Dental-Sealants.png\"]\r\n[divider height=\"25\"]\r\n<h3>Dental Sealants</h3>\r\n[divider height=\"10\"]\r\n<p align=\"justify\">Dental sealants are clear coatings applied to the surfaces of a child’s molars to prevent the development of tooth decay. They work by preventing food and plaque from resting in the grooves and crevices of molars – an area especially susceptible to cavities.</p>\ncenter\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n30px 15% 15px\nborder-right: 1px solid #eff6fa;\n\nBox\n[image src=\"http://richmonddental.iugale.tech/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Dental-Implants.png\"]\r\n[divider height=\"25\"]\r\n<h3>Dental implants</h3>\r\n[divider height=\"10\"]\r\n<p align=\"justify\">Dental implants are surgical-grade root devices that support permanent tooth prosthetics that are manufactured to last a lifetime. These artificial roots are anchored in the bone beneath the gums where they become fused into the jaw. A crown is mounted atop the implant for a long-lasting and natural looking smile.. </p>\ncenter\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n30px 15% 15px\n\nBox\n[image src=\"http://richmonddental.iugale.tech/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Dentures.png\"]\r\n[divider height=\"25\"]\r\n<h3>Dentures</h3>\r\n[divider height=\"10\"]\r\n<p align=\"justify\">Dentures are an effective and affordable way of replacing missing teeth. Composed of a durable plastic resin and sometimes porcelain, both partial and full dentures can be fabricated to look and feel natural. Today’s dentures are custom-fit to make it possible to eat foods with confidence and speak articulately.</p>\ncenter\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n30px 15% 15px\nborder-right: 1px solid #eff6fa;\n\nBox\n[image src=\"http://richmonddental.iugale.tech/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Removable-Dentures.png\"]\r\n[divider height=\"25\"]\r\n<h3>Removable Dentures</h3>\r\n[divider height=\"10\"]\r\n<p align=\"justify\">Dentures are removable tooth prosthetics designed to look and function like natural teeth. For thousands of years, some form of denture has been used to fill in the gaps left by missing teeth, although today’s dentures are much more advanced and easier to care for. </p>\ncenter\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n30px 15% 15px\nborder-right: 1px solid #eff6fa;\n\nBox\n[image src=\"http://richmonddental.iugale.tech/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Bite-Guards.png\"]\r\n[divider height=\"25\"]\r\n<h3>Bite Guard</h3>\r\n[divider height=\"10\"]\r\n<p align=\"justify\">A bite guard is a dental appliance custom-fit to a patient’s teeth. Bite guards serve varying purposes and are often recommended for use in patients of all ages. It is important that bite guards be professionally fit, rather than purchased over the counter, as this ensures maximum comfort and protection during wear.</p>\ncenter\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n30px 15% 15px\n\ndefault\n\nBox\n[image src=\"http://richmonddental.iugale.tech/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Crowns-and-Bridges.png\"]\r\n[divider height=\"25\"]\r\n<h3>Crowns and Bridges</h3>\r\n[divider height=\"10\"]\r\n<p align=\"justify\">Dental crowns and bridges are custom-fitted tooth prosthetics that are used to replace or restore damaged or missing teeth. Crowns – also known as caps – are fixed over the surfaces of natural tooth structures or dental implants.</p>\ncenter\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n30px 15% 15px\nborder-right: 1px solid #eff6fa;\n\nBox\n[image src=\"http://richmonddental.iugale.tech/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Partial-Dentures.png\"]\r\n[divider height=\"25\"]\r\n<h3>Partial Dentures</h3>\r\n[divider height=\"10\"]\r\n<p align=\"justify\">Like a bridge, partial dentures rest on surrounding teeth to fill in the gaps where one or more teeth are missing. But unlike a bridge, partial dentures are fully removable by the wearer. Partials are affordable alternatives to other types of dental prosthetics and are custom-made to blend in with each patient’s natural teeth.</p>\ncenter\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n30px 15% 15px\nborder-right: 1px solid #eff6fa;\n\nBox\n[image src=\"http://richmonddental.iugale.tech/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/compsite-tooth-colored-fillingsfull-mouth-restoration.png\"]\r\n[divider height=\"25\"]\r\n<h3>Composite Tooth-Colored FillingsFull Mouth Restoration</h3>\r\n[divider height=\"10\"]\r\n<p align=\"justify\">Composite fillings – also known as tooth-colored fillings – are dental restorations designed to be inconspicuous and natural in appearance. They blend well with the teeth and appear more natural than amalgam fillings, which are darker and more easily seen by other people.</p>\ncenter\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n30px 15% 15px\n\ndefault\n\nBox\n[image src=\"http://richmonddental.iugale.tech/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/PFM-Restoration.png\"]\r\n[divider height=\"25\"]\r\n<h3>PFM Restorations</h3>\r\n[divider height=\"10\"]\r\n<p align=\"justify\">Porcelain fused to metal, or PFM restorations have been a standard in restorative dentistry for more than three decades. During that time, dentists around the world have adopted PFM crowns and bridges due to the versatility for use, as well as their ability to be matched to surrounding teeth.</p>\ncenter\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n30px 15% 15px\nborder-right: 1px solid #eff6fa;\n\nBox\n[image src=\"http://richmonddental.iugale.tech/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Provisional-Restorations.png\"]\r\n[divider height=\"25\"]\r\n<h3>Provisional Restorations </h3>\r\n[divider height=\"10\"]\r\n<p align=\"justify\">Provisional restorations are often used during complex restorative dental procedures to serve as temporary prosthetic replacements while patients wait for a permanent restoration. Provisional restorations offer patients to try-out the look and feel of the final prosthetic and make any necessary changes before the final fabrication and fitting.</p>\ncenter\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n30px 15% 15px\nborder-right: 1px solid #eff6fa;\n\nBox\n[image src=\"http://richmonddental.iugale.tech/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Tooth-Extractions.png\"]\r\n[divider height=\"25\"]\r\n<h3>Tooth Extractions</h3>\r\n[divider height=\"10\"]\r\n<p align=\"justify\">Tooth extractions are routine dental procedures used to remove decayed, damaged or otherwise problematic teeth. Dentists usually make every effort to preserve natural teeth, although sometimes an extraction is necessary. Although the procedure is performed in a dentist’s or oral surgeon’s office, it is considered surgery.</p>\ncenter\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n30px 15% 15px\n\nBox\n[image src=\"http://richmonddental.iugale.tech/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Sports-Mouth-Guard.png\"]\r\n[divider height=\"25\"]\r\n<h3>Sports Mouth Guards</h3>\r\n[divider height=\"10\"]\r\n<p align=\"justify\">Dental mouth guards have long been used to protect the teeth, gums and supporting tissues from damage, injury and trauma. There are two types of sports mouth guards – over the counter and custom.</p>\ncenter\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n30px 15% 15px\nborder-right: 1px solid #eff6fa;\n\nBox\n[image src=\"http://richmonddental.iugale.tech/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Dental-cleaning-and-Consultation.png\"]\r\n[divider height=\"25\"]\r\n<h3>Dental Cleaning & Consultation</h3>\r\n[divider height=\"10\"]\r\n<p align=\"justify\">Preventative care is a foundation of dentistry. The American Dental Association recommends visiting your dentist regularly – usually about twice yearly – for full cleanings, examinations, and consultations for potential treatment. Professional dental cleanings help remove built-up plaque that is not removable using conventional brushing and flossing.</p>\ncenter\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n30px 15% 15px\nborder-right: 1px solid #eff6fa;\n\nBox\n[image src=\"http://richmonddental.iugale.tech/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Cosmetic-dentistry.png\"]\r\n[divider height=\"25\"]\r\n<h3>Cosmetic Dentistry</h3>\r\n[divider height=\"10\"]\r\n<p align=\"justify\">Your smile is the first impression that others have of you, so it makes sense that you would want it to be bright, white and healthy. According to the American Academy of Cosmetic Dentistry, more than 99 percent of all American adults believe that a smile is an important asset for social situations.</p>\ncenter\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n30px 15% 15px\n\ndefault\n\nBox\n[image src=\"http://richmonddental.iugale.tech/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/General-Dentistry.png\"]\r\n[divider height=\"25\"]\r\n<h3>General Dentistry</h3>\r\n[divider height=\"10\"]\r\n<p align=\"justify\">General dentistry encompasses a broad range of diseases and disorders of the oral and maxillofacial region. Everyone should see a general dentist for routine oral health examinations, twice-yearly cleanings, and treatment of routine oral health complications, such as minor tooth decay. General dentistry is as much about prevention as it is about treatment.</p>\ncenter\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n30px 15% 15px\nborder-right: 1px solid #eff6fa;\n\nBox\n[image src=\"http://richmonddental.iugale.tech/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Teeth-whitening.png\"]\r\n[divider height=\"25\"]\r\n<h3>Teeth Whitening</h3>\r\n[divider height=\"10\"]\r\n<p align=\"justify\">Teeth whitening procedures are used to brighten the appearance of a patient’s smile – sometimes by as many as 5 to 10 shades in a single session. According to the American Dental Association, teeth whitening procedures have become some of the most popular esthetic dental treatments among patients throughout the country, including.</p>\ncenter\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n30px 15% 15px\nborder-right: 1px solid #eff6fa;\n\nBox\n[image src=\"http://richmonddental.iugale.tech/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Untitled-22.png\"]\r\n[divider height=\"25\"]\r\n<h3>Veneers  and Laminates </h3>\r\n[divider height=\"10\"]\r\n<p align=\"justify\">Dental veneers – also known as laminates – are used to cosmetically enhance the appearance of one or more teeth. Veneers are very thin, porcelain or resin shells that are customized for a desirable color and shape. They are bonded to the surface of the teeth to reshape broken, misshapen or irregular teeth.</p>\ncenter\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n30px 15% 15px\n\n400\ndefault\n\nHeading + desc\n<h2>Need an Emergency Help? Call Us!</h2>\r\n<h3 class=\"themecolor\"> +91 6360 743 827</h3>\r\n[divider height=\"15\"]\r\n<p>Clinic No : 543, RP Building, Langford Road,<br/>\r\nOppo. Karnataka Hockey Stadium, Banglore - 560027</p>\r\n[divider height=\"15\"]\r\n[button title=\"Contact us\" link=\"http://richmonddental.iugale.tech/contact-us/\" align=\"\" icon=\"\" icon_position=\"\" color=\"theme\" font_color=\"\" size=\"2\" full_width=\"\" class=\"\" download=\"\" rel=\"\" onclick=\"\"]\nno-repeat;left top;;\nauto\n\n'),(119,14,'mfn-post-hide-content','0'),(120,14,'mfn-post-slider','0'),(121,14,'mfn-post-slider-layer','0'),(122,14,'mfn-post-hide-title','1'),(123,14,'mfn-post-remove-padding','1'),(124,14,'mfn-post-custom-layout','0'),(125,14,'mfn-post-one-page','0'),(126,14,'mfn-post-menu','0'),(127,14,'slide_template','default'),(128,14,'mfn-page-items',''),(129,14,'mfn-page-items-seo','Heading + desc\n<h1>Doctors</h1>\r\n[divider height=\"15\"]\r\n<p align=\"justify\">Our well trained Dentists and staffs with the latest advance equipment are ready to get the extra smile on your fac